TITLE: Where to travel 2022: The best destinations to visit
SUMMARY: Travel has taken a hard hit since the pandemic. Still, there are signs of hope. From a culturally rich city in the American Plains to a small African nation full of national parks, here are the 22 best destinations to visit in 2022.

TITLE: The latest on coronavirus pandemic and Omicron variant
SUMMARY: More than 100,000 people are currently hospitalized with Covid-19 in the US for the first time in nearly four months, data shows. Follow here for the latest news updates.

TITLE: Motorists have been stranded on a major interstate in Virginia since last night
SUMMARY: Numerous motorists have been stranded from Monday into Tuesday on Interstate 95 in eastern Virginia -- some for well over a dozen hours -- because of a severe winter storm that has sent authorities scrambling to clear paths to get them out.

TITLE: Biden set to announce US will double its order of Pfizer's antiviral pill to treat Covid-19
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden is expected to announce Tuesday he is doubling the US order for Pfizer's Covid-19 antiviral pill, Paxlovid, when he receives a briefing from his Covid-19 response team and delivers remarks on the Omicron variant.

TITLE: Hackers breached Florida health care system, potentially exposing data on 1.3 million people
SUMMARY: Hackers breached the computer networks of a southeast Florida health care system in October and may have accessed sensitive personal and financial information on over 1.3 million people, the health care system announced this week.

TITLE: NYC Mayor Eric Adams to big banks: We need you back in the office
SUMMARY: New York City Mayor Eric Adams is not pleased with the shift back to remote work by Wall Street banks and other major employers in the Big Apple.

TITLE: No winners in Powerball drawing as jackpot grows to $610 million
SUMMARY: There were no winners in Monday night's Powerball drawing for an estimated $522 million.

TITLE: Manchin delivers blow to Democrats as he signals opposition to changing Senate rules to advance voting bill
SUMMARY: Sen. Joe Manchin of West Virginia, the pivotal Senate swing vote, made clear on Tuesday that he remains deeply skeptical of overhauling the chamber's rules on a simple majority basis to advance voting legislation, a clear sign that a frantic push by Democrats to win his support to change the filibuster and pass one of the party's core priorities is likely doomed.

TITLE: Classic BlackBerry phones stop working today
SUMMARY: You can no longer use that old BlackBerry phone sitting at the bottom of your drawer somewhere.

TITLE: What is 'flurona' and how serious is it?
SUMMARY: Israel's first known case of a person infected with Covid-19 and the flu has been detected, the country's Ministry of Health confirmed to CNN on Tuesday, raising questions over how the two viruses might impact someone who contracts them at the same time.

TITLE: Covid-19 hospitalizations soar past the Delta peak and creep toward the all-time high
SUMMARY: In just four weeks, Omicron jumped from an estimated 8% of new Covid-19 infections to an estimated 95% of new infections, according to the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention.

TITLE: Meet the new dog breeds officially recognized by the American Kennel Club
SUMMARY: 2022 is off to a great start for dog lovers, thanks to the addition of two new dog breeds -- the Russian Toy and the Mudi -- by the American Kennel Club.

TITLE: Judge expects to make decision on motion to dismiss lawsuit against Prince Andrew soon
SUMMARY: An attorney for Prince Andrew argued at a hearing Tuesday that a lawsuit filed against his client by Virginia Giuffre, who alleges the prince sexually abused her, should be dismissed largely because he believes a settlement agreement Giuffre signed with Jeffrey Epstein releases Andrew from legal action.

TITLE: Jimmy Fallon says he tested positive for Covid-19
SUMMARY: Jimmy Fallon is opening up about his experience with Covid-19.

TITLE: Seth Meyers cancels week of 'Late Night' shows after testing positive for Covid-19
SUMMARY: Another NBC late night show has been disrupted by the pandemic.

TITLE: Biden's infrastructure czar urges governors to appoint their own infrastructure implementation coordinators
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden's infrastructure czar Mitch Landrieu sent letters to all the nation's governors on Tuesday urging them to appoint their own infrastructure implementation coordinators to smooth the rollout of the $1.2 trillion law.

TITLE: 'This Is Us' cast is feeling emotional about the show's final season too
SUMMARY: We are just hours away from the sixth and final season of "This Is Us."

TITLE: Update to CDC's Covid-19 isolation guidance is imminent, source says
SUMMARY: The US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention is expected to update its guidance on the recommended isolation period imminently, according to a source familiar with the plan.

TITLE: Virginia storm leaves motorists stranded on I-95
SUMMARY: Drivers have been stranded for hours on a major interstate in eastern Virgina -- some stuck from Monday into Tuesday morning -- after a severe winter storm caused massive backups. Follow here for live updates.

TITLE: Albany DA declines to prosecute former Gov. Andrew Cuomo on forcible touching charge
SUMMARY: The Albany district attorney will not prosecute former New York Gov. Andrew Cuomo on a misdemeanor sex crime charge of forcible touching after reviewing the evidence in the case despite finding the complainant "cooperative" and "credible."

TITLE: The stock market sure is acting strangely
SUMMARY: Wall Street is having a topsy-turvy moment. Long-term Treasury yields have shot up dramatically, and investors in stocks are cheering the bond market's big moves. That doesn't happen often. So what gives?

TITLE: French TV star Igor Bogdanoff dies of Covid, days after twin brother
SUMMARY: French TV star Igor Bogdanoff has died of Covid-19, six days after his twin brother Grichka died due to the same disease, the brothers' lawyer confirmed to CNN Tuesday.

TITLE: Almost 600 Amazon packages found dumped near Oklahoma City
SUMMARY: The Oklahoma County Sheriff's Office says they are investigating how almost 600 packages from Amazon ended up dumped in a rural area northeast of Oklahoma City.

TITLE: In the year since the US Capitol attack, judges remind us what it means to be American
SUMMARY: On January 6, rioters streamed past the federal courthouse in Washington, DC, and descended upon the US Capitol. For weeks after the attack, DC's chief judge said she could see National Guard troops from the window in her chambers.

TITLE: 3 key takeaways from the Elizabeth Holmes verdict
SUMMARY: The verdict is a stark rebuke of the defense, which attempted to portray Holmes as a visionary leader who fell victim to subordinates who misled her and investors who misunderstood her.

TITLE: Donald Trump can't get enough of 'strong' authoritarians
SUMMARY: On Monday night, former President Donald Trump endorsed Viktor Orban, the prime minister of Hungary, for reelection.

TITLE: What should I do if my flight has been canceled or delayed?
SUMMARY: Here are some expert tips about what travelers should do when flights are delayed or canceled.

TITLE: The world's 500 richest people became $1 trillion richer last year
SUMMARY: The world's wealthiest people, whose fortunes already strained comprehension, collectively gained $1 trillion last year, according to Bloomberg's Billionaires Index.

TITLE: Areas from Nashville to New York will be hit by another round of snow later this week
SUMMARY: The early week storm -- that brought up to a foot of snow in some places in the east and stranded motorists on a major interstate -- has pushed off the East Coast. Now another system -- that hasn't formed quite yet -- will round out the week with additional snowfall -- this time, New York City could be in the mix.

TITLE: Melania Trump to auction white hat and other items for $250,000 minimum bid
SUMMARY: Melania Trump announced Tuesday morning that she is holding an auction of the white hat she wore during the visit of the French first family, the Macrons, to the White House in 2018.
